HEADWORD: Disobedience
<hw>Dis`o*be"di*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Neglect or
refusal to obey; violation of a command or prohibition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is undutiful to him other actions, and lives in open
<qex>disobedience</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

